snippet.title: Baaji | Coke Studio Bangla | Season 3 | Emon Chowdhury X Hashim Mahmud
snippet.description:
Beyond sight and sound, love unites us across cultures, oceans, and mountains. Love knows no borders or differences. #Baaji is an eternal quest that bridges barriers and reaches every soul.  
Urban poet Hashim Mahmud’s heartfelt verses and melody, combined with the eclectic music arrangement of Emon Chowdhury, creates a soulful celebration of love’s journey. The song honors Bangladesh’s diverse indigenous cultures, each unique but united in harmony. #RealMagic happens when we embrace diversity and let our hearts beat together in unity. 

ভালোবাসায় এক হয় সব, মুছে যায় সাগর আর পাহাড়ের অসীম দূরত্ব, ঘুচে যায় সীমানা কিংবা ভাষার ব্যাবধান। #Baaji এমনই এক গল্প, যে সকল বাধা পেরিয়ে স্পর্শ করে সবার মন।      
কবি হাশিম মাহমুদের হৃদয় থেকে আসা কথামালা ও সুর এবং ইমন চৌধুরীর মনোমুগ্ধকর সংগীত আয়োজনে #Baaji এক অমলিন ভালোবাসার গল্প।
গানটিতে তুলে ধরা হয়েছে বাংলাদেশের নানা সংস্কৃতি ও ঐতিহ্যকে। এভাবেই যখন আমরা ভিন্নতাকে গ্রহণ করি তখনই হয় #RealMagic। 

#CokeStudioBangla #BanglaMusic 

Listen on Spotify: https://tinyurl.com/2m4avecy

snippet.title: Obak Bhalobasha | Coke Studio Bangla | Season 3 | Warfaze
snippet.description:
There are songs that fade with time, and then there is this masterpiece. #ObakBhalobasha isn't just a song; it’s a love affair within the starlight, whispered by the wind, burning bright for generations. This timeless piece has been the track to teenage dreams, kindling senses, and pure joy since the 90’s.
Entering on their 40th year, Warfaze, one of the pioneer bands of rock music in our industry, re-envisions this golden track. This love affair started when the lead vocalist penned the lyrics amidst the crashing waves on a seashore of Cox’s Bazar- the longest uninterrupted natural beach in the world. 
This new rendition, a tribute to the cult classic, accompanied by a choir, a stringed orchestra and a heavily distorted guitar riff, Warfaze creates the harmonious symphony of nostalgia. A nostalgia that sparks the same fire in the hearts of youth today as it did for their parents and elder siblings. It reminds us of the #RealMagic of love and nature that is like the spirit of youth, truly timeless.

#CokeStudioBangla #BanglaMusic 

Listen on Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/track/1qG2wN8k7rY0vNpuTMjOlI

snippet.title: Ma Lo Ma | Coke Studio Bangla | Season 3 | Pritom Hasan X Sagor Dewan X Arif Dewan X Aly Hasan
snippet.description:
#MALOMA embodies the realisation that life is a journey where the inevitability of adulting and nostalgia work as two sides of a coin. As we grow up, there comes a time echoing the question: "What am I doing here?" But within this very questioning lies the potential for a beautiful transformation, a self-acceptance that allows us to bloom even in the most demanding seasons. This folk fusion song serves as a conversation acknowledging this inevitable shift, using the metaphor of a broken boat symbolising life and a river symbolising the world.
In addition, the song is infused with ‘Chaad Petano Gaan’ (Roofing Music by Masons), a form of ’Shaari Gaan’ (Music of the Boatmen and other worker groups) from the folk genre tracing back to the Mughal Era. An urban version of this was found among building masons around the 80s and 90s, who migrated to cities for livelihood and sang these verses while working to construct concrete roofs. The beats of the paddles, combined with the verses, break monotony, and create a festive atmosphere around their hard work.
Pritom takes up the song, infusing his twist, alongside the duo from the Dewan family: Shagor Dewan and Arif Dewan, whose ancestor is the original writer of the song Ma Lo Ma Jhi Lo Jhi. Rapper Aly Hasan joins in and conveys his optimistic perception to create this #RealMagic. Together, it becomes a timeless tale of growth, adulthood, and the eternal quest for meaning in an ever-changing world.

#CokeStudioBangla #BanglaMusic 

Listen on Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/album/5sPD4vRlLz4X4CvJRxdYpJ

Curated & Produced by Shayan Chowdhury Arnob

localized.title: Ma Lo Ma | Coke Studio Bangla | Season 3 | Pritom Hasan X Sagor Dewan X Arif Dewan X Aly Hasan
localized.description:
#MALOMA embodies the realisation that life is a journey where the inevitability of adulting and nostalgia work as two sides of a coin. As we grow up, there comes a time echoing the question: "What am I doing here?" But within this very questioning lies the potential for a beautiful transformation, a self-acceptance that allows us to bloom even in the most demanding seasons. This folk fusion song serves as a conversation acknowledging this inevitable shift, using the metaphor of a broken boat symbolising life and a river symbolising the world.
In addition, the song is infused with ‘Chaad Petano Gaan’ (Roofing Music by Masons), a form of ’Shaari Gaan’ (Music of the Boatmen and other worker groups) from the folk genre tracing back to the Mughal Era. An urban version of this was found among building masons around the 80s and 90s, who migrated to cities for livelihood and sang these verses while working to construct concrete roofs. The beats of the paddles, combined with the verses, break monotony, and create a festive atmosphere around their hard work.
Pritom takes up the song, infusing his twist, alongside the duo from the Dewan family: Shagor Dewan and Arif Dewan, whose ancestor is the original writer of the song Ma Lo Ma Jhi Lo Jhi. Rapper Aly Hasan joins in and conveys his optimistic perception to create this #RealMagic. Together, it becomes a timeless tale of growth, adulthood, and the eternal quest for meaning in an ever-changing world.

#CokeStudioBangla #BanglaMusic 

Listen on Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/album/5sPD4vRlLz4X4CvJRxdYpJ
